---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Rawan Aladdin — For Islands"
  description="A targeted mini-portfolio: why Rawan Aladdin belongs on the Islands team."
  bodyClass="islands-pitch"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/islands.css" />
  </Fragment>

  <main>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         HERO
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="hero" class="ip-section" style="min-height: 100vh; justify-content: flex-end; padding-bottom: 9rem;">
      <p class="ip-hero-label">For Islands — May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="ip-hero-h1">Hi Islands,<br>I'm Rawan.</h1>
      <p class="ip-hero-sub">
        UX designer and developer who ships AI products — and moves at startup speed.
      </p>
      <div class="ip-hero-links">
        <a href="https://rawanaladdin.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="main-link">rawanaladdin.com ↗</a>
        <a href="mailto:hello@rawanaladdin.com" class="main-link">hello@rawanaladdin.com ↗</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="ip-divider"></div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         WHY ISLANDS
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="why-islands" class="ip-section">
      <p class="ip-section-label">Why Islands</p>
      <h2 class="ip-h2">Three reasons<br>I belong here.</h2>
      <div class="ip-cards">

        <div class="ip-card">
          <p class="ip-card-num">01</p>
          <h3>I designed it and built it.</h3>
          <p>
            On Onward, I was lead developer and designer. I made the architecture decisions,
            wrote the code, and shipped the product. When something needed to change,
            I didn't wait — I changed it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="ip-card">
          <p class="ip-card-num">02</p>
          <h3>I come from both sides of the screen.</h3>
          <p>
            Started in Computer Science, moved to design at BCIT. I prototype in Figma
            and write the code that ships it. That means I speak developer fluently
            and hand off work that actually builds.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="ip-card">
          <p class="ip-card-num">03</p>
          <h3>My design decisions have data behind them.</h3>
          <p>
            Onward scored 8/10 in usability testing with 12 users. That number drove
            a redesign of the feedback flow before we shipped. I ask "how do we know?"
            before I call something done.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="ip-divider"></div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         PROJECT 01: ONWARD
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="onward" class="ip-section">
      <p class="ip-section-label">Project 01 — AI Interview Coaching App</p>
      <div class="ip-two-col">

        <div class="ip-media-col">
          <img src="/clipstart.gif" alt="Onward app — interview session starting" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="ip-stats">
            <div class="ip-stat-block">
              <span class="ip-stat" data-count="200" data-suffix="+">200+</span>
              <span class="ip-stat-label">Professionals presented to, live</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ip-stat-block">
              <span class="ip-stat" data-static="true">8/10</span>
              <span class="ip-stat-label">Ease of use in user testing</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <img
            src="/clipinterview-results.gif"
            alt="Onward app — interview results screen"
            loading="lazy"
            style="margin-top: 1.75rem;"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="ip-text-col">
          <h2 class="ip-h2">Onward</h2>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">The Problem</p>
          <p>
            Internationally-educated healthcare workers — fully qualified, years of experience —
            fail Canadian job interviews not because of skill gaps, but communication barriers:
            language anxiety, cultural unfamiliarity with STAR-method expectations,
            the quiet fear of being misunderstood.
          </p>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">My Role</p>
          <p>
            Lead developer and designer. I owned the product end-to-end — architecture decisions,
            design system, user research, and the final pitch to angel investors at VANTEC Network.
          </p>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">Key Decisions</p>
          <ul class="ip-decisions">
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Split the timer.</strong> Practice mode
              shows elapsed time — no pressure. Mock mode counts down — real stakes. One insight,
              two modes, zero ambiguity.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Real-time filler word detection</strong>
              via Azure Speech-to-Text surfaces patterns without shaming — the feedback is data,
              not judgment.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">STAR method scaffolding</strong> guides
              without restricting. The AI leads structure, the user decides content.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Loading states for every async action.</strong>
              When Azure processes speech, Onward shows it. Trust is built in the micro-moments.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="ip-outcome">
            <p>
              <strong>Shipped in 4 months.</strong> Pitched to VANTEC Network angel investors.
              Presented live to 200+ professionals, investors, and government officials.
              Continues in active development at onward-prep.ca.
            </p>
          </div>

          <a href="/onward" class="ip-case-link">Read the full case study ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Aunt interview: the human story behind Onward -->
      <div class="ip-clip-block">
        <p class="ip-sub-label">Hear why we built this</p>
        <div class="ip-clip-row">
          <div class="ip-media-block ip-video-wrapper" title="Click to watch with sound">
            <video id="onward-clip-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline>
              <source src="/clip.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            </video>
            <div class="ip-video-hint">▶ click for sound &amp; fullscreen</div>
          </div>
          <div class="ip-clip-photo-wrap">
            <div class="ip-clip-caption">Pitching live to 200+ professionals</div>
            <img src="/presentation.webp" alt="Rawan pitching Onward live" class="ip-clip-photo" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="ip-divider"></div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         PROJECT 02: SAFECYCLE
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="safecycle" class="ip-section">
      <p class="ip-section-label">Project 02 — Cycling Safety MVP</p>
      <div class="ip-two-col">

        <div class="ip-media-col">
          <img src="/safecycle-coded.gif" alt="SafeCycle app — live coded prototype" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="ip-stats">
            <div class="ip-stat-block">
              <span class="ip-stat" data-static="true">4</span>
              <span class="ip-stat-label">Months to MVP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ip-stat-block">
              <span class="ip-stat" data-static="true">3</span>
              <span class="ip-stat-label">Roles — PM, Design, Dev</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <img
            src="/safecycle-wireframes.webp"
            alt="SafeCycle wireframes"
            loading="lazy"
            style="margin-top: 1.75rem;"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="ip-text-col">
          <h2 class="ip-h2">SafeCycle</h2>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">The Problem</p>
          <p>
            Cyclists and pedestrians in Vancouver — especially those with mobility needs —
            have no routing tool built around safety. Existing apps optimise for speed,
            not hazard avoidance or accessibility.
          </p>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">My Role</p>
          <p>
            Project manager, UX designer, and lead developer. Three hats, one four-month sprint.
            The goal was a functional MVP — not a production app — so every decision was about
            validating the concept with working code, not over-engineering it.
          </p>

          <p class="ip-sub-label">Key Decisions</p>
          <ul class="ip-decisions">
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Scoped ruthlessly.</strong>
              An MVP only works if you ship it. We cut every feature that wasn't core to the
              safety routing problem and shipped something testable in 4 months.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Google Maps API over custom routing.</strong>
              Building our own routing infrastructure would have taken the whole semester.
              Using an existing API meant we could focus on the UX problem, not the plumbing.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: white; font-weight: 500;">Accessibility as the core thesis,</strong>
              not a stretch goal. Wheelchair routing and hazard avoidance were first-class
              requirements — if we cut those, we'd built the wrong product entirely.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <a href="/safecycle" class="ip-case-link">Read the full case study ↗</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="ip-divider"></div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         ABOUT
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="about" class="ip-section" style="min-height: auto; padding-top: 6rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
      <p class="ip-section-label">About</p>
      <div class="ip-about-inner">
        <p>
          Vancouver-based UX designer and developer. Started in Computer Science,
          found design, and never looked back.
        </p>
        <p>
          I completed a Diploma in Digital Design & Development at BCIT and I'm finishing
          a Bachelor of Creative Industries — design practice, emerging tech, creative strategy.
          I've shipped live AI products as lead developer, led a digital media team, and built
          enough in code to know why implementation constraints are design constraints.
        </p>
        <p>
          I care about the whole product — not just the interface. When I open Figma,
          I already know what the dev handoff looks like.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="ip-divider"></div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
         CTA
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="cta" class="ip-section ip-cta" style="min-height: 70vh;">
      <h2 class="ip-cta-h2">Let's build something.</h2>
      <p class="ip-cta-sub">
        I'd love to work with Islands on products that move fast without losing
        what makes them good.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@rawanaladdin.com" class="ip-email-link">hello@rawanaladdin.com ↗</a>
      <p class="ip-secondary-links">
        <a href="https://rawanaladdin.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rawanaladdin.com</a>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/rawan-aladdin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/rawan-aladdin</a>
      </p>
      <div class="ip-also">
        <p class="ip-also-label">Also worth a look</p>
        <a href="/playground" class="ip-also-link">Playground — where I experiment when no one's watching ↗</a>
        <a href="/projects" class="ip-also-link">Full portfolio ↗</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <script is:inline src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.7/gsap.min.js"></script>
  <script is:inline src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.7/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>
  <script defer src="/js/islands.js"></script>

</BaseLayout>
